The board of Eskom will on Tuesday announce disciplinary measures against its former acting CE in a bid by the power utility to clean up its corruption-tainted image. The disciplinary measures stem from an investigation into allegations of conflict of interest involving hundreds of millions or rand on the part of Matshela Koko. The investigation found substantial evidence of wrongdoing and irregularities in contracts involving a company in which Koko’s stepdaughter has an interest. If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link below to go to the full article: Eskom plans to take action against Koko If you would like to subscribe  to BusinessLIVE Premium to read the full story, please click here